4.9.25  4:34 am   Why is it so customary for lyrics in music to rhyme? Does the human brain just find that pleasing for whatever reason?

      it's way way way way way way more pleasing when you don't think about this. without thinking about this, your rhythms wouldn't even have to land in such a way that they'd want to rhyme. or, if there are spots that do line up like that, then it will happen automatically, to the extent that it is pleasing. Rhyming on purpose is total sabotage, in my opinion. nature wants to bring you all kinds of goodies, most of which are so much deeper and richer than someone's default obligatory notion of a 'rhyme'

4.8.25  10:39 pm   I have a lot of short instrumental pieces that I am having trouble expanding into full songs, but I've decided to not force them into something longer. I know that the only way for these pieces to have a chance to be seen is to do videos, but I have no idea what to do considering they are instrumentals without lyrics which is something already working against the chances of them being heard. What do you suggest doing?

      videos are a perfect home for instrumental music. you can get people to secretly love the video, AND secretly love the music, when they perhaps would not have fallen for either one individually. If you can't figure out what to do, find some simple method of doing 10 different videos for the same piece of music. you'll never find out what works until you try a bunch of things
